Document: ButtonGroup  
Path: godot/classes/class_buttongroup.rst  
Summary: Class for managing groups of buttons, typically used for radio button functionality.  

The `ButtonGroup` class is used to manage groups of buttons, ensuring only one button can be selected at a time, commonly used for radio button implementations. It inherits from `Control < Control >` and provides methods to add, remove, and manage buttons within the group. Key properties include `exclusive` (boolean) to enforce single selection, `selected_button` (NodePath) to reference the currently selected button, and `buttons` (Array) to list all buttons in the group.  

Methods include:  
- `add_button(button: Button)`: Adds a button to the group.  
- `remove_button(button: Button)`: Removes a button from the group.  
- `set_selected_button(button: Button)`: Sets the selected button.  
- `get_selected_button() -> Button`: Returns the currently selected button.  

Note: All buttons added to the group must be of type `Button`.  
Warning: Modifying the group while iterating over its buttons may cause unexpected behavior.  
Tip: Use `exclusive` to enable/disable single-selection behavior.  

GDScript:  
```gdscript  
var group = ButtonGroup.new()  
group.exclusive = true  
group.add_button($Button1)  
group.add_button($Button2)  
```  

C#:  
```csharp  
var group = new ButtonGroup();  
group.Exclusive = true;  
group.AddButton(Button1);  
group.AddButton(Button2);  
```  

Enum values:  
- `BUTTON_GROUP_MODE_EXCLUSIVE`: Enforces single selection (default).  
- `BUTTON_GROUP_MODE_MULTIPLE`: Allows multiple selections.
