Document: ButtonGroup
Path: godot/classes/class_buttongroup.rst
Summary: A group of BaseButton-derived buttons that function like radio buttons, allowing only one button to be pressed at a time.

A group of BaseButton-derived buttons. The buttons in a ButtonGroup are treated like radio buttons: No more than one button can be pressed at a time. Some types of buttons (such as CheckBox) may have a special appearance in this state. Every member of a ButtonGroup should have BaseButton.toggle_mode set to true. Note: BaseButton-derived buttons in a group must have their toggle_mode property enabled to function correctly. Inherits: BaseButton
---CHUNK---
Document: ButtonGroup
Path: godot/classes/class_buttongroup.rst
Summary: Properties and their default values for the ButtonGroup class

Properties:
- allow_unpress (bool): Controls if the group can have no buttons pressed. Default: false
- resource_local_to_scene (bool): Overrides Resource's property to always treat resource as local to scene. Default: true (overrides Resource's resource_local_to_scene property)
